Git & GitHub Main Commands Cheat Sheet
1. Configure Git
Set username
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
Used to set your Git username.

Set email
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
Used to set your Git email.

Check configuration
git config --list
Shows all Git settings.

2. Initialize & Clone Repository
Initialize a new repository
git init
Creates a new local Git repository.

Clone an existing repository
git clone <repo-url>
Downloads a GitHub repository to your system.

Example:

git clone https://github.com/user/project.git
3. Check Repository Status
Check current status
git status
Shows:

modified files

staged files

untracked files

4. Add Files
Add a single file
git add filename
Add all files
git add .
Add all tracked modified files
git add -u
5. Commit Changes
Commit staged changes
git commit -m "message"
Example:

git commit -m "Added login page"
Add + commit together
git commit -am "message"
Works only for already tracked files.

6. View Commit History
Show commit history
git log
Compact history
git log --oneline
Graph view
git log --oneline --graph --all
7. Branch Commands
Create branch
git branch branch-name
List branches
git branch
Switch branch
git checkout branch-name
Create and switch together
git checkout -b branch-name
Modern switch command
git switch branch-name
Create and switch (modern)
git switch -c branch-name
Delete branch
git branch -d branch-name
Force delete branch
git branch -D branch-name
8. Merge Commands
Merge branch into current branch
git merge branch-name
Used after switching to target branch.

Example:

git checkout main
git merge feature-login
9. Remote Repository Commands
Add remote repository
git remote add origin <repo-url>
View remotes
git remote -v
Remove remote
git remote remove origin
Change remote URL
git remote set-url origin <new-url>
10. Push Commands
First push
git push -u origin main
Push changes
git push
Push specific branch
git push origin branch-name
Force push
git push --force
Safer force push
git push --force-with-lease
11. Pull & Fetch Commands
Pull latest changes
git pull
Pull specific branch
git pull origin main
Fetch changes only
git fetch
Fetch all branches
git fetch --all
Difference:

pull = fetch + merge

fetch = download only

12. Undo Commands
Unstage file
git restore --staged filename
Discard file changes
git restore filename
Reset last commit (keep changes)
git reset --soft HEAD~1
Reset last commit (remove changes)
git reset --hard HEAD~1
Reset to specific commit
git reset --hard <commit-id>
13. Stash Commands
Save temporary changes
git stash
View stashes
git stash list
Apply stash
git stash apply
Apply and remove stash
git stash pop
Delete stash
git stash drop
14. Rebase Commands
Rebase current branch
git rebase main
Interactive rebase
git rebase -i HEAD~3
Used to:

squash commits

edit commits

clean history

15. Tag Commands
Create tag
git tag v1.0
List tags
git tag
Push tag
git push origin v1.0
Push all tags
git push --tags
16. File Difference Commands
Show differences
git diff
Show staged differences
git diff --staged
Compare commits
git diff commit1 commit2
17. GitHub Authentication
Login using GitHub CLI
gh auth login
Clone using SSH
git clone git@github.com:user/repo.git
Generate SSH key
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "you@example.com"
Test SSH connection
ssh -T git@github.com
18. GitHub CLI Commands
Install GitHub CLI
Linux:

sudo apt install gh
Create repository
gh repo create
Create pull request
gh pr create
View pull requests
gh pr list
Clone repository
gh repo clone user/repo
19. Remove Files from Git
Remove tracked file
git rm filename
Remove cached file only
git rm --cached filename
20. Useful Advanced Commands
Show who changed each line
git blame filename
Search commit message
git log --grep="keyword"
Clean untracked files
git clean -f
Clean directories too
git clean -fd
Cherry-pick commit
git cherry-pick <commit-id>
21. Common Full Workflow
New Project
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin <repo-url>
git push -u origin main
Daily Workflow
git pull
git add .
git commit -m "Updated feature"
git push
Branch Workflow
git checkout -b feature-auth
git add .
git commit -m "Added auth"
git push origin feature-auth
